title: Grateful Dead Live at Cameron Indoor Stadium, Duke University on 1982-04-02
lineage: Master Cassettes (Nakamichi CR-7A)> Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) > Tascam Hi-Res Editor (.wav 24-bit/96k) > Adobe Audition CC 2025 > DDi Codec (dolby B) > TLH flac2496
description:
Set I
New Minglewood Blues >
Sugaree
Mama Tried >
Mexicali Blues
Loser
Little Red Rooster
Candyman
Looks Like Rain
China Cat Sunflower >
I Know You Rider
Set II
Samson & Delilah
It Must Have Been The Roses
Man Smart (Woman Smarter)
He's Gone >
Truckin' >
Drums >
Space >
The Other One >
Black Peter >
Sugar Magnolia
Don't Ease Me In

Comment
Jerry and Phil swap sides of the stage and remain that way until the last show in 1995

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text:
DDi codec makes all the difference! Thanks Scott! This recording/show needed it.

This show has the last(?) good ole fashioned monstrous He's Gone > Truckin' >(d/s) >Other One, and that's worth a listen.
